caption.text:
Be concentrations (mg/kg) in eluates from the 7-step sequential extraction of core P4 at five depths. The seven steps represent the: 1) water soluble phase; 2) exchangeable phase; 3) easily reducible minerals; 4) resistant reducible minerals; 5) easily oxidizable minerals (e.g. secondary sulfides); 6) resistant oxidizable minerals (e.g. primary sulfides); and 7) residues and silicates. The zones are based on what was presented in
Fig. 1
.
